{"_attachments":{},"_id":"node-plop","_rev":"267675-61f1b3e5efbf788ede8e1c72","author":{"name":"Andrew Worcester","email":"andrew@amwmedia.com","url":"http://amwmedia.com"},"description":"programmatic plopping for fun and profit","dist-tags":{"latest":"0.32.3"},"license":"MIT","maintainers":[{"name":"crutchcorn","email":"crutchcorn@gmail.com"},{"name":"amwmedia","email":"andrew@amwmedia.com"}],"name":"node-plop","readme":"# Node-Plop\n\n[![npm](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/node-plop.svg)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-plop)\n[![GitHub actions](https://img.shields.io/github/workflow/status/plopjs/node-plop/test)](https://github.com/plopjs/node-plop/actions/workflows/test.yml)\n\nThis is an early publication of the plop core logic being removed from the CLI tool. Main purpose for this is to make it easier for others to automate code generation through processes and tools OTHER than the command line. This also makes it easier to test the code functionality of PLOP without needing to test via the CLI interface.\n\nThis is the backend code that drives the plop CLI tool using node-plop.\n\n```javascript\nimport nodePlop from \"node-plop\";\n// load an instance of plop from a plopfile\nconst plop = await nodePlop(`./path/to/plopfile.js`);\n// get a generator by name\nconst basicAdd = plop.getGenerator(\"basic-add\");\n\n// run all the generator actions using the data specified\nbasicAdd.runActions({ name: \"this is a test\" }).then(function (results) {\n  // do something after the actions have run\n});\n```\n","time":{"created":"2022-01-26T20:49:41.103Z","modified":"2025-09-26T19:00:55.841Z","0.30.0":"2021-11-27T20:17:07.475Z","0.30.0-alpha.1":"2021-11-24T09:58:04.785Z","0.26.3":"2021-10-18T05:55:00.011Z","0.26.2":"2020-07-31T20:29:53.870Z","0.26.1":"2020-07-19T21:59:22.958Z","0.26.0":"2020-05-21T15:51:52.882Z","0.25.0":"2020-03-03T02:46:32.247Z","0.24.0":"2020-02-17T19:51:59.088Z","0.23.0":"2019-11-04T19:27:29.613Z","0.22.0":"2019-10-18T17:25:08.456Z","0.21.0":"2019-